terms.medium_def:
A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.25.26; 
referred to as Israel or [ ] or Israelite or "God" (KJV= Israel) (יִשְׂרָאֵל), or Israel (Aramiac יִשְׂרָאֵל), or Jacob or "he" (KJV= Jacob) (יַעֲקֹב), or Jeshurun (יְשֻׁרוּן), or Israelite (יִשְׂרְאֵלִי), or Israelitess (יִשְׂרְאֵלִית), or Israel or Israelite (Ἰσραήλ), or Jacob (Ἰακώβ), or Israelite or Israel (Ἰσραηλίτης); 
son of Isaac and Rebekah; 
a brother of Esau; 
husband of Rachel, Leah, Zilpah and Bilhah; 
father of Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Dan, Naphtali, Gad, Asher, Issachar, Zebulun, Dinah, Joseph and Benjamin. § a symbolic name for Israel describing her ideal character

A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, only mentioned at 1Ch.2.18; 
only referred to as Jesher (יֶ֫שֶׁר); 
son of Caleb and Azubah(?); 
a brother of Hur, Shobab, Ardon, Mesha, Haran, Moza, Gazez, Sheber, Tirhanah, Regem(?), Jotham(?), Geshan(?), Pelet(?), Ephah(?), Shaaph(?), Shaaph, Sheva and Achsah. § one of the sons of Caleb and grandson of Hezron by wife Azubah

A location first mentioned at 1Ch.27.29; 
referred to as Sharon (שָׁרוֹן), or Sharonite (שָׁרוֹנִי), or Sharon (KJV= Saron) (Σάρων). § Sharonite, of Sharon "a plain"
inhabitant of the district of Sharon
